<h3>Track Featured Snippet Wins</h3>
<p>Every featured snippet you hold is a potential voice search answer. Track your snippet count monthly. Set a target to win 5 to 10 new featured snippets per month by adding structured Q&amp;A content to existing pages.</p>
<h3>Monitor Question Queries</h3>
<p>In <a href="/blog/google-search-console-guide/">Google Search Console</a>, filter your queries by questions. Look for searches starting with "how," "what," "where," "when," "why," and "who." Track impressions and clicks for these queries over time. Rising question-query traffic signals increasing voice search visibility.</p>
<h3>Voice Search Traffic Estimation</h3>
<p>A rough estimation method: take your total featured snippet traffic and assume 20 to 30% originates from voice devices. This is not precise, but it provides a directional metric for tracking voice search growth.</p>
